WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.141 --> 00:00:11.077
KAREN: So what does it mean
to be truly authentic,

00:00:11.077 --> 00:00:14.481
and how does this idea
of authenticity impact

00:00:14.481 --> 00:00:17.984
what it means to be
whole or personhood?

00:00:17.984 --> 00:00:20.653
And so, like, looking at
yourself, how do you identify,

00:00:20.653 --> 00:00:23.590
and how is your identity
your chosen identity

00:00:23.590 --> 00:00:28.328
based on your conceptualization
of what it means

00:00:28.328 --> 00:00:30.430
to be authentically something?

00:00:30.430 --> 00:00:33.466
Does, like, how you
define authenticity

00:00:33.466 --> 00:00:36.870
and your relationship to
authenticity impact how

00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.872
you choose to identify?

00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:41.341
RACHEL: And sort of as an extension
of this-- and these kind of

00:00:41.341 --> 00:00:41.841
go together.

00:00:41.841 --> 00:00:44.310
That's why we're
saying them together.

00:00:44.310 --> 00:00:46.980
Do the languages, or does
the language that you speak,

00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:49.649
or that your
ancestors spoke affect

00:00:49.649 --> 00:00:52.152
this concept of authenticity?

00:00:52.152 --> 00:00:56.156
So if you're the son of someone
whose parents spoke a language,

00:00:56.156 --> 00:00:58.291
but you don't speak it, do
you feel less authentic,

00:00:58.291 --> 00:01:01.728
or does it make you feel more
authentic in some manner?

00:01:01.728 --> 00:01:03.930
Or are there linguistic
discourses of power

00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:05.999
that affect how you
perceive the roles

00:01:05.999 --> 00:01:08.435
that the languages that you
speak or that of your ancestors

00:01:08.435 --> 00:01:12.872
spoke affect your
choice of identity--

00:01:12.872 --> 00:01:18.078
and how authenticity of my
language plays a role in it?

00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:20.080
KAREN: Should we present
the second question?

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.115
MICHEL DEGRAFF: I think we
should start answering, right?

00:01:22.115 --> 00:01:23.015
So thank you so much.

00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:37.759
AUDIENCE: I guess I don't
mind answering first.

00:01:37.764 --> 00:01:39.399
So I guess the first thing--

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:49.440
so I'll answer one and two,
but I'll start with two,

00:01:49.442 --> 00:01:51.644
because this is something
that I always think about--

00:01:51.644 --> 00:01:56.583
is the fact that I don't speak
Spanish makes me less authentic

00:01:56.583 --> 00:01:59.419
in whatever Hispanic or
Mexican identity I have,

00:01:59.419 --> 00:02:01.788
because I'm not able--

00:02:01.788 --> 00:02:03.823
I feel like I wasn't
allowed to identify

00:02:03.823 --> 00:02:05.792
with the Hispanic or
Mexican community,

00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:07.127
because I didn't speak Spanish.

00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:09.062
And like, you
know, growing up, I

00:02:09.062 --> 00:02:10.597
guess it was different
for my mother.

00:02:10.597 --> 00:02:14.267
It didn't matter to her, and
I guess at that timeframe,

00:02:14.267 --> 00:02:17.904
you know, whatever
the population-- like,

00:02:17.904 --> 00:02:21.941
Spanish is becoming a very
profound language in the US,

00:02:21.941 --> 00:02:25.578
and so, like, maybe
during my mother's time

00:02:25.578 --> 00:02:27.680
there weren't a whole lot
of Spanish speakers, so,

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:29.082
like, for her, it didn't matter.

00:02:29.082 --> 00:02:30.583
And like, my
grandmother growing up,

00:02:30.583 --> 00:02:32.252
it was, like, not
OK for her to speak,

00:02:32.252 --> 00:02:35.321
and so I feel like it's
different for my mother

00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:37.724
because she doesn't care.

00:02:37.724 --> 00:02:39.792
Honestly, I don't know how
I should ask my mom how

00:02:39.792 --> 00:02:42.629
she identifies with herself,
but it's very different

00:02:42.629 --> 00:02:45.265
because, for me, I do feel like
that was important whereas it

00:02:45.265 --> 00:02:46.399
wasn't important for her.

00:02:46.399 --> 00:02:49.769
And I still don't feel authentic
in my Hispanic or Mexican

00:02:49.769 --> 00:02:52.505
identity, because I don't
speak the language--

00:02:52.505 --> 00:02:55.742
and that maybe, in some
ways, speaking the language

00:02:55.742 --> 00:02:57.510
would allow me to
identify more with,

00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:02.649
like, the culture, because
I feel like it's important.

00:03:02.649 --> 00:03:06.186
And then I guess,
overall, authentic,

00:03:06.186 --> 00:03:08.888
I honestly hate thinking
of it like that,

00:03:08.888 --> 00:03:11.791
because I am so
un-authentic then,

00:03:11.791 --> 00:03:15.562
because I'm African-American,
I'm white, and I'm Hispanic,

00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:20.433
and nobody considers me
authentic because it's like,

00:03:20.433 --> 00:03:23.369
how can you be
authentic if being--

00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:25.171
I feel like being
authentic, in this way,

00:03:25.171 --> 00:03:27.040
means, like, having to
identify specifically

00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:31.010
with one or another, and you
can't authentically be all--

00:03:31.010 --> 00:03:32.312
you can't be more than one.

00:03:32.312 --> 00:03:35.081
I don't know if
that makes sense.

00:03:35.081 --> 00:03:37.183
And I guess for me, it's
just like my identity,

00:03:37.183 --> 00:03:41.921
I just have to pick and choose
what I liked, what was OK,

00:03:41.921 --> 00:03:43.555
and some of it has
been imposed on me.

00:03:43.555 --> 00:03:47.327
There are aspects of my identity
that I didn't get to choose

00:03:47.327 --> 00:03:50.763
and that I'm trying to change,
because like now feeling woke,

00:03:50.763 --> 00:03:54.033
I guess, and learning about
different aspects of my culture

00:03:54.033 --> 00:03:58.805
and history regarding
whatever it may be,

00:03:58.805 --> 00:04:01.941
I feel like I'm trying to
change aspects of my identity

00:04:01.941 --> 00:04:04.477
that were not--

00:04:04.477 --> 00:04:06.980
yeah, I hope those
answered your questions.

00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:10.016
I got really flustered, because
there's this camera over here.

00:04:10.016 --> 00:04:13.052
Normally, it wouldn't
matter, but yeah--

00:04:13.052 --> 00:04:14.587
so I hope that
answers your question.

