00:06:33.426 --> 00:06:37.029
was intended for a person.

00:06:37.029 --> 00:06:40.533
It's very much like one
of those adjectives that's

00:06:40.533 --> 00:06:42.969
for inanimate objects, you know?

00:06:42.969 --> 00:06:45.138
It's like for things
that don't have--

00:06:45.138 --> 00:06:45.772
AUDIENCE: Gold.

00:06:45.772 --> 00:06:48.107
AUDIENCE: Yeah like gold,
like authentic, like something

00:06:48.107 --> 00:06:49.542
that you can define.

00:06:49.542 --> 00:06:51.544
Like, OK, if something's
authentically gold,

00:06:51.544 --> 00:06:53.579
that means it's 100% gold.

00:06:53.579 --> 00:06:57.016
But you can't put
bounds on things

00:06:57.016 --> 00:07:01.120
like people, and cultures,
and identities to the point

00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:03.122
where you have a
concrete definition,

00:07:03.122 --> 00:07:07.693
because no person's ever going
to get that perfect definition.

00:07:07.693 --> 00:07:10.029
MICHEL DEGRAFF: But it has
always been the tendency

00:07:10.029 --> 00:07:14.500
to try to quantize these--

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:16.269
so you mentioned gold, right.

00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:20.273
So in the history of Haiti,
there was this famous French--

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:21.874
she was Creole French,
meaning that she

00:07:21.874 --> 00:07:24.277
was of French ancestry, but
he was born in the Caribbean.

00:07:24.277 --> 00:07:28.881
His name was [INAUDIBLE],, and
he added one chapter where he

00:07:28.881 --> 00:07:30.950
created this calculus of--

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:36.422
he could compute 128 parts
of black versus white.

00:07:36.422 --> 00:07:40.092
So he had this calculus of if
you half black, half white,

00:07:40.092 --> 00:07:41.194
then you're mulatto.

00:07:41.194 --> 00:07:45.231
If you're quarter black
with three quarters white,

00:07:45.231 --> 00:07:46.599
then you're Quadroon.

00:07:46.599 --> 00:07:47.800
And he had terms.

00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:50.603
He had adjectives--
talking about adjectives--

00:07:50.603 --> 00:07:53.139
he had adjectivves for
each of these categories,

00:07:53.139 --> 00:07:55.241
but how do you compute that?

00:07:55.241 --> 00:08:01.547
How can you look at someone and
decide that they are 128 black

00:08:01.547 --> 00:08:03.449
versus the rest, white?

00:08:03.449 --> 00:08:05.952
But there was this
strong belief somebody

00:08:05.952 --> 00:08:07.887
that you could do
that, and that actually

00:08:07.887 --> 00:08:10.990
each of these
partitions would define

00:08:10.990 --> 00:08:13.392
[INAUDIBLE] biological reasons.

00:08:13.392 --> 00:08:15.161
But if you were half
black, half white,

00:08:15.161 --> 00:08:16.229
you would behave
like this, or you

00:08:16.229 --> 00:08:18.197
would have physical
properties from these lines.

00:08:18.197 --> 00:08:20.366
But if you were one quarter
white and three quarters black,

00:08:20.366 --> 00:08:22.835
then you could predict what
your behavior and your physique

00:08:22.835 --> 00:08:24.303
would actually look like.

00:08:24.303 --> 00:08:31.043
Think of Jim Crow in the US,
so one drop of black blood--

00:08:31.043 --> 00:08:37.850
one drop of black blood would
make you non-white, right?

00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:40.820
But it's good to have people
to think of it in these terms

00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:44.423
and try to remove ourself
from this cognition.

00:08:47.120 --> 00:08:49.160
